## event
](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/event)

The event package contains all the events:  [Alarm](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Alarm),  [Alert](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Alert), &amp;  [Reminder](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Reminder); which can be added to  [clock.Timeline](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Timeline). To create a new event, create the  [EventFactory](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#EventFactory) and specify the event you&#39;d like to create.

### [**Event**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/event/Event.java)

This is the interface that is used to create  [Alarm](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Alarm),  [Alert](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Alert), &amp;  [Reminder](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Reminder). Each Event will have a trigger that sends out anActionEvent. This allows your interface to listen to the timeline events. If you&#39;re to create your own event it must trigger anActionEvent. The recommended practice is to add your event before it is suppose to be triggered. You may, but not suggested, call the ActionEvent&#39;s separate from the event. The action will still be recorded in  [record.Records](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Records)

**Must implement methods:**

- trigger():void
- compareTo():int

### [**EventFactory**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/event/EventFactory.java)

This is where you&#39;ll want to create your Events that will be added to  [clock.Timeline](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/tree/master/docs#Timeline). You may extend this class to add custom Events that aren&#39;t supported by default.

### [**EventList**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/event/EventList.java)

This is what the Timeline uses to hold all the Events for the future. It will hold any amount and always sort the events to the closest current time.

### [**Alarm**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/event/Alarm.java)

This is one of three default events, this triggers the Ring event. You must pass three parameters into the class: Date time,String action, &amp; String entity.

### [**Alert**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/event/Alert.java)

This is the second of three default events, this triggers the Notify event and also trigger the type of event. The type is either RED or YELLOW (case insensitive). You must pass four parameters into the class: Date time, String action, String entity &amp; String type.

### [**Reminder**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/event/Reminder.java)

This is the third of the default events, this triggers the Ring event. You must pass three parameters into the class: Date time, String action, &amp; String entity.

## report
](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/report)

The report package contains everything you&#39;ll need to generate and build reports that are requested from the User. The Assumption here is that the Researchers have their own way of generating reports that are specific for themselves. This package only contains reports for the User.

UML:  ![](data:image/*;base64,)

### [**Report**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/report/Report.java)

This is the interface that you can use to build custom reports. You must have build():void and toString():String methods. When a report is created it must trigger an ActionEvent and called Generating Report [reportName]. Within your report you must request all data from the researchers, as all records are stored on their side.

### [**ReportFactory**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/report/ReportFactory.java)

This is where you&#39;ll request all your reports that you&#39;d like to be created. It is preferred when adding custom reports to extend this class.

### [**SleepReport**](https://github.com/hhsnopek/csc341-final/blob/master/src/report/SleepReport.java)

This is the only default report that is provided. This will grab all the sleeping data: Sleep Time, Alerts to Sleep, Wake up Alarms, Wake up Time, and a bunch more information.
